**Segments**

- Based on type, the Clinical Trial Management System (CTMS) market can be segmented into enterprise-based CTMS and site-based CTMS. Enterprise-based CTMS are commonly used to manage multiple clinical trial sites and are often deployed by pharmaceutical companies and contract research organizations (CROs). Site-based CTMS, on the other hand, are utilized by individual research sites to track and manage their own clinical trials independently.
- On the basis of delivery mode, the CTMS market can be categorized into web-based (cloud-based) CTMS, licensed CTMS, and on-premise (installed) CTMS. Web-based CTMS solutions have gained popularity due to their easy accessibility, cost-effectiveness, and scalability, making them a preferred choice for many research organizations.
- By component, the CTMS market is divided into software and services. The software segment includes features such as patient recruitment, randomization, trial planning, monitoring, and reporting. The services segment comprises implementation, integration, training, and support services provided by CTMS vendors to ensure smooth deployment and operation of the system.

